01:23:41,815 --> 01:23:44,045
"Ferdy's Bar."

971
01:23:46,353 --> 01:23:49,015
"Come by after. Natalie."

972
01:24:02,936 --> 01:24:04,927
I'll have a beer, please.

973
01:24:05,005 --> 01:24:06,996
- What do you want? - A beer, please.

974
01:24:07,074 --> 01:24:09,508
You can't just waltz in here dressed like that and ask for a beer.

975
01:24:09,576 --> 01:24:11,942
- What, is there a dress code? - Why are you here?

976
01:24:12,012 --> 01:24:14,981
- I'm meeting someone called Natalie. - Well, that's me.

977
01:24:15,049 --> 01:24:18,541
Yeah. We met before, right?

978
01:24:18,619 --> 01:24:20,883
- Then why am I here? - I don't know. Tell me.

979
01:24:20,954 --> 01:24:23,252
I don't remember. I have no short-term memory. It's not amnesia.

980
01:24:23,323 --> 01:24:26,190
- Oh, you're the memory guy. - How do you know about me?

981
01:24:26,260 --> 01:24:28,728
My boyfriend told me about you.

982
01:24:28,796 --> 01:24:32,732
- Yeah? Who's your boyfriend? - Jimmy Grants. Do you know him?

983
01:24:32,800 --> 01:24:35,360
No.

984
01:24:35,436 --> 01:24:38,894
Well, he knows you. He told me about you.

985
01:24:38,972 --> 01:24:41,065
He said you were staying at the Discount.

986
01:24:41,141 --> 01:24:44,508
In fact, a cop came by here earlier looking for you.

987
01:24:44,578 --> 01:24:47,274
Said he was looking for a guy who can't remember anything, wouldn't know how he got here...

988
01:24:47,347 --> 01:24:49,281
or what he'd done.

989
01:24:49,349 --> 01:24:51,510
Said I get a lot of guys around here like that.

990
01:24:51,585 --> 01:24:55,043
Well, you know, chronic alcoholism is one cause of short-term memory loss.

991
01:24:57,124 --> 01:24:59,854
- Are you Teddy? - No. My name is Leonard.

992
01:24:59,927 --> 01:25:02,054
- Did Teddy send you? - I don't know.

993
01:25:02,129 --> 01:25:06,327
- What's happened to Jimmy? - I don't know that either.

994
01:25:06,400 --> 01:25:08,766
- Sorry. - You don't remember anything?

995
01:25:08,836 --> 01:25:12,203
You don't remember where you've been or what you've just done.

996
01:25:12,272 --> 01:25:15,901
No. I can't make new memories. Everything just fades.

997
01:25:15,976 --> 01:25:18,672
- Then why did you come here? - I found this in my pocket.

998
01:25:21,982 --> 01:25:24,780
Your pocket.

999
01:25:39,299 --> 01:25:42,200
[Clearing Throat]

1000
01:25:48,142 --> 01:25:51,270
Bar bet. Care to contribute?

1001
01:25:51,345 --> 01:25:54,212
- No, thanks. - It's for a lot of money.

1002
01:25:54,281 --> 01:25:57,216
Come on. Proceeds are going to charity. Help me out.

1003
01:26:02,289 --> 01:26:04,314
[Hawking]

1004
01:26:09,496 --> 01:26:11,293
Thank you.

1005
01:26:28,215 --> 01:26:30,308
- On the house. - Thanks.

1006
01:26:30,384 --> 01:26:34,343
[Man Laughing]

1007
01:26:34,588 --> 01:26:38,615
It's completely fucked because nobody believes you.

1008
01:26:38,692 --> 01:26:41,957
It's amazing what a little brain damage will do for your credibility.

1009
01:26:42,029 --> 01:26:44,827
I guess it's some kind of poetic justice for not believing Sammy.

1010
01:26:44,898 --> 01:26:47,833
You know the truth about my condition, officer?

1011
01:26:47,901 --> 01:26:49,994
You don't know anything.

1012
01:26:50,070 --> 01:26:52,231
You feel angry, you don't know why.

1013
01:26:52,306 --> 01:26:56,003
You feel guilty, you have no idea why.

1014
01:26:56,076 --> 01:26:58,476
You could do anything and not have the faintest idea ten minutes later.

1015
01:26:58,545 --> 01:27:01,537
Like Sammy. I could have done something like Sammy.

1016
01:27:01,615 --> 01:27:05,813
I didn't tell you... what happened to Sammy and his wife?

1017
01:27:05,886 --> 01:27:07,820
Well, she came to see me at my office.

1018
01:27:07,888 --> 01:27:09,822
I thought she was just trying to catch me off guard,

1019
01:27:09,890 --> 01:27:12,825
so I didn't tell her what I really thought, but I never said that he was faking,

1020
01:27:12,893 --> 01:27:14,827
just that his condition was mental, not physical.

1021
01:27:14,895 --> 01:27:17,830
I found out later that she went home and gave Sammy his final exam.

1022
01:27:19,566 --> 01:27:22,501
Sammy? It's time for my shot.

1023
01:27:38,485 --> 01:27:41,579
She knew beyond a doubt that he loved her.

1024
01:27:41,655 --> 01:27:44,089
So she found a way to test him.

1025
01:27:50,564 --> 01:27:53,032
[Sighs]

1026
01:27:56,336 --> 01:27:59,931
Sammy. It's time for my shot.

1027
01:28:00,007 --> 01:28:03,238
Hmm.

1028
01:28:09,917 --> 01:28:13,785
- She really thought she'd call his bluff. - There you go.

1029
01:28:13,854 --> 01:28:18,951
Or she just didn't wanna live with the things she put him through.

1030
01:28:28,001 --> 01:28:32,529
Sammy. It's time for my shot.

1031
01:28:38,679 --> 01:28:40,476
It won't hurt.

1032
01:29:24,591 --> 01:29:27,719
She went into a coma and never recovered.

1033
01:29:27,794 --> 01:29:32,026
- Sammy couldn't understand or explain what happened. - Oh!

1034
01:29:32,099 --> 01:29:34,158
He's been in a home ever since.

1035
01:29:34,234 --> 01:29:37,635
He doesn't even know that his wife's dead.

1036
01:29:37,704 --> 01:29:41,105
I was wrong about Sammy, and I was wrong about his wife.

1037
01:29:41,174 --> 01:29:43,108
She wasn't interested in the money.

1038
01:29:43,176 --> 01:29:45,337
She just needed to understand his problem.

1039
01:29:45,412 --> 01:29:48,904
His brain didn't respond to conditioning. But he wasn't a con man.

1040
01:29:48,982 --> 01:29:52,349
And when she looked into his eyes, she thought he could be the same person.

1041
01:29:52,419 --> 01:29:54,819
When I looked into his eyes, I thought I saw recognition.

1042
01:29:54,888 --> 01:29:57,015
Now I know. You fake it.

1043
01:29:57,090 --> 01:30:00,025
If you're supposed to recognize somebody, you just pretend to.

1044
01:30:00,093 --> 01:30:02,789
You bluff it to get a pat on the head from the doctors.

1045
01:30:02,863 --> 01:30:05,559
You bluff it to seem less of a freak.

1046
01:30:08,835 --> 01:30:10,894
What drug dealer?

1047
01:30:10,971 --> 01:30:13,804
[Tires Screeching]

1048
01:30:36,296 --> 01:30:39,424
- Hey, Lenny, how you doing? - It's private back here.

1049
01:30:39,499 --> 01:30:42,525
- It's okay. We know each other. Right, kid? - How did you know I was here?

1050
01:30:42,602 --> 01:30:44,593
Oh, the Jag is out front. You should have put it around back.

1051
01:30:44,671 --> 01:30:47,697
What are you still doing here? There's plenty of tattoo parlors up north.

1052
01:30:47,774 --> 01:30:51,266
I just wanted to get something down before it slipped my mind.

1053
01:30:51,344 --> 01:30:53,335
- Then give me the keys. I'll move it for you. - It'll be all right for a minute.

1054
01:30:53,413 --> 01:30:55,677
- Wait out there. - Oh, for Christ...

1055
01:30:55,749 --> 01:30:58,684
Look, give me a minute. I gotta get something for you.

1056
01:31:01,621 --> 01:31:06,285
Fact six. Car license SG 137IU.

1057
01:31:12,165 --> 01:31:15,259
Look. Wait a minute, will ya?

1058
01:31:17,938 --> 01:31:20,463
- All right, we gotta get you out of here. - Why?

1059
01:31:20,540 --> 01:31:23,475
Aw, man. Come on, Leonard. How many times I gotta tell you?

1060
01:31:23,543 --> 01:31:25,807
- It's not safe for you to hang around here anymore. - Why not?

1061
01:31:25,879 --> 01:31:27,813
Because that cop's looking for you.

1062
01:31:27,881 --> 01:31:30,475
Now, I gotta get you a new identity, some new clothes.

1063
01:31:30,550 --> 01:31:32,711
A different car would do for now. So put these on.

1064
01:31:32,786 --> 01:31:35,778
Whoa, whoa. What cop?

1065
01:31:35,856 --> 01:31:38,825
He's a bad cop. He's the one who checked you into the Discount Inn.

1066
01:31:38,892 --> 01:31:41,759
He's been calling you for days, telling you shit, slipping envelopes under your door.

1067
01:31:41,828 --> 01:31:45,559
- How do you know this? - He told me. He thinks it's funny.

1068
01:31:45,632 --> 01:31:47,566
- He's been laughing at you. - You're full of shit.

1069
01:31:47,634 --> 01:31:50,569
I'm not. He knows you're no good on the phone, so he's been calling you up.

1070
01:31:50,637 --> 01:31:52,628
Sometimes you don't answer the phone,

1071
01:31:52,706 --> 01:31:55,504
so he slips shit under your door to scare you into answering the phone again,

1072
01:31:55,575 --> 01:31:57,770
giving you a line of crap about John G. Being some local drug dealer.

1073
01:31:57,844 --> 01:32:01,610
- Jimmy Grants. - Who's Jimmy Grants?

1074
01:32:01,681 --> 01:32:03,649
Leonard, Jimmy's the drug dealer.

1075
01:32:03,717 --> 01:32:06,015
The cop wants to know how his operation's run.

1076
01:32:06,086 --> 01:32:08,111
He's got some score in mind. Somehow you're involved.

1077
01:32:08,188 --> 01:32:10,850
Uh-huh. How do you know him?

1078
01:32:10,924 --> 01:32:15,657
I'm a snitch. He's a cop from out of town. The local boys put us together.

1079
01:32:15,729 --> 01:32:18,095
If he knew I was helping you, he'd fucking kill me.

1080
01:32:18,165 --> 01:32:21,965
So take these clothes, put them on and get the fuck out of here.

1081
01:32:22,035 --> 01:32:24,663
Come on, Leonard. Just go.

1082
01:32:44,224 --> 01:32:46,158
You are full of shit.

1083
01:32:48,962 --> 01:32:51,658
[Thinking] "Come by after. Natalie."

1084
01:32:51,731 --> 01:32:53,665
"Ferdy's Bar."

1085
01:33:34,541 --> 01:33:37,772
- [Knocking On Window] - Hey, Jimmy.

1086
01:33:39,346 --> 01:33:42,713
I'm sorry. I, uh, thought you were somebody else.

1087
01:33:42,782 --> 01:33:44,716
Sorry.

1088
01:33:44,784 --> 01:33:46,843
That's okay.

1089
01:34:00,166 --> 01:34:05,001
So this Jimmy Grants deals drugs out of the bar where his girlfriend works?

1090
01:34:05,071 --> 01:34:08,598
But he's not gonna bring her along. He'll come by himself, right?

1091
01:34:08,675 --> 01:34:12,873
I always figured the drugs angle would be the best way to get him.

1092
01:34:12,946 --> 01:34:16,541
No, officer. I'm as ready as I'll ever be.

1093
01:34:16,616 --> 01:34:19,380
You're in the lobby? What do you look like?

1094
01:34:20,654 --> 01:34:22,622
I'll be right there.

1095
01:35:04,731 --> 01:35:06,665
Lenny.

1096
01:35:08,968 --> 01:35:11,300
Officer Gammell.

1097
01:35:12,539 --> 01:35:15,235
Yeah. Come on.

1098
01:35:31,091 --> 01:35:36,552
- Hey, smile. - Oh, don't... Not here. Over here.

1099
01:35:42,502 --> 01:35:45,528
- Now, is it Officer or Lieutenant Gammell? - You know what?

1100
01:35:45,605 --> 01:35:48,039
Don't write Gammell, just Teddy.

1101
01:35:48,108 --> 01:35:50,542
- Why? - I'm undercover.

1102
01:35:53,380 --> 01:35:55,814
This is the directions where he's going.

1103
01:35:55,882 --> 01:35:58,908
- My number's on the bottom if you need me. - You're not coming?

1104
01:35:58,985 --> 01:36:00,919
No. It wouldn't be appropriate.

1105
01:36:05,458 --> 01:36:09,224
Nice picture. I look thin.

1106
01:36:11,765 --> 01:36:15,667
Hey, Lenny. Make him beg.

1107
01:37:20,733 --> 01:37:24,829
[Vehicle Approaching]

1108
01:37:38,017 --> 01:37:39,951
[Man] Teddy!

1109
01:37:42,422 --> 01:37:44,617
Hey, Teddy!

1110
01:37:47,560 --> 01:37:49,357
Teddy!

1111
01:37:51,664 --> 01:37:53,598
Jimmy.

1112
01:37:53,666 --> 01:37:55,657
What the fuck are you doing here?

1113
01:37:55,735 --> 01:37:59,296
- You Jimmy Grants? - Expecting any other Jimmy's out here, Memory Man?

1114
01:37:59,372 --> 01:38:03,638
- Do you remember me? - Yeah, I remember you.

1115
01:38:03,710 --> 01:38:06,508
Where the fuck's Teddy? Well?

1116
01:38:11,050 --> 01:38:13,814
Motherfuck... What the fuck are you doing?

1117
01:38:15,955 --> 01:38:19,015
- Strip. - You're making a big fucking mistake, pal.

1118
01:38:19,092 --> 01:38:22,061
Strip!

1119
01:38:22,128 --> 01:38:26,155
- My associates are not the kind of people you wanna piss off. - Don't say anything else.

1120
01:38:26,232 --> 01:38:29,224
- I knew I couldn't trust that fuck! - Take it off.

1121
01:38:33,473 --> 01:38:37,807
- Your pants too. - Why?

1122
01:38:37,877 --> 01:38:40,209
I don't wanna get blood on them.

1123
01:38:40,280 --> 01:38:43,306
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Wait, wait, wait. Did he tell you what I was bringing?

1124
01:38:43,383 --> 01:38:47,319
- Take your fuckin' pants off! - I've got two hundred grand stashed in the car!

1125
01:38:47,387 --> 01:38:50,083
- Just take it! - You think you can bargain with me?

1126
01:38:50,156 --> 01:38:52,522
- Just take the money and walk away! - I don't want your money!

1127
01:38:52,592 --> 01:38:55,026
Then what?

1128
01:38:55,094 --> 01:38:58,393
- What do you want from me? - I want my fuckin' life back!

1129
01:40:29,856 --> 01:40:31,824
Sammy.

1130
01:40:37,864 --> 01:40:39,923
[Thinking] He said "Sammy." How does he know about Sammy?

1131
01:40:39,999 --> 01:40:41,864
Oh, fuck.

1132
01:41:01,954 --> 01:41:05,219
[Thinking] What have I done?

1133
01:41:05,291 --> 01:41:08,556
Hey, mister, I need help. There's a guy in here, he's hurt bad.

1134
01:41:08,628 --> 01:41:11,461
- We gotta get him to a doctor. - All right.

1135
01:41:12,699 --> 01:41:14,633
I don't know what happened.

1136
01:41:14,701 --> 01:41:18,034
- I've got this memory thing. Do I know you? - No. Don't worry. I'm a cop.

1137
01:41:18,104 --> 01:41:21,403
- Is he still breathing? - I don't know. Maybe.

1138
01:41:21,474 --> 01:41:23,499
What the hell were you guys doing down here?

1139
01:41:23,576 --> 01:41:26,511
Well, I don't remember. I have this condition.

1140
01:41:26,579 --> 01:41:29,980
Well, I hope it's not as serious as his, 'cause this guy's dead.

1141
01:41:30,049 --> 01:41:33,075
Ouch! Lenny! That shit kills!

1142
01:41:33,152 --> 01:41:36,212
- So you remember me now, huh? - You are a fuckin' cop.

1143
01:41:36,289 --> 01:41:38,655
Yeah. And I'm the guy that helped you find him.

1144
01:41:38,725 --> 01:41:40,693
Get up. Get up.

1145
01:41:40,760 --> 01:41:43,228
Lenny, you got the wrong idea.

1146
01:41:45,932 --> 01:41:47,957
Who is that? He knew me.

1147
01:41:48,034 --> 01:41:50,696
Of course he did. He raped your wife. He fucked up your brain.

1148
01:41:50,770 --> 01:41:52,795
Bullshit. He's not the guy.

1149
01:41:52,872 --> 01:41:57,241
His name is James F. Grants. John G. Check your tattoos.

1150
01:41:57,310 --> 01:42:00,746
- What was he bringing the two hundred grand for? - What?

1151
01:42:00,813 --> 01:42:04,112
- What was it for? - A load of amphetamines I told him I had.

1152
01:42:04,183 --> 01:42:07,914
- Is this a drug deal? - No. Yeah, that and your thing.

1153
01:42:07,987 --> 01:42:09,921
Look, Leonard, Jimmy's your guy.

1154
01:42:09,989 --> 01:42:12,457
- I just figured we'd make a few dollars on the side. - How did he know me?

1155
01:42:12,525 --> 01:42:15,085
The Discount Inn. He dealt out of there.

1156
01:42:15,161 --> 01:42:18,460
The guy at the front desk let him know if anybody came snooping around.

1157
01:42:18,531 --> 01:42:20,590
He called Jimmy the minute he saw you taking a picture of the dump.

1158
01:42:20,666 --> 01:42:23,567
- You're fucking using me. - No! You get half!

1159
01:42:23,636 --> 01:42:26,264
He knew about Sammy! Why would I tell him about fuckin' Sammy?

1160
01:42:26,339 --> 01:42:29,740
You tell everybody about Sammy, everybody who'll listen.

1161
01:42:29,809 --> 01:42:31,936
"Remember Sammy Jankis?" "Remember Sammy Jankis?"

1162
01:42:32,011 --> 01:42:34,946
Great story. It gets better every time you tell it.

1163
01:42:35,014 --> 01:42:37,812
So you lie to yourself to be happy.

1164
01:42:37,884 --> 01:42:39,943
There's nothing wrong with that. We all do it.

1165
01:42:40,019 --> 01:42:43,147
Who cares if there's a few little details you'd rather not remember?

1166
01:42:45,591 --> 01:42:47,957
- What the fuck are you talking about? - I don't know.

1167
01:42:48,027 --> 01:42:51,394
Your wife's surviving the assault.

1168
01:42:51,464 --> 01:42:55,400
Her not believing your condition. The torment and pain and anguish...

1169
01:42:55,468 --> 01:42:58,130
tearing her up inside.

1170
01:42:58,204 --> 01:43:00,729
The insulin.

1171
01:43:00,807 --> 01:43:03,503
That's Sammy, not me. I told you about Sammy.

1172
01:43:03,576 --> 01:43:06,602
Yeah, right. Like you tell yourself over and over again.

1173
01:43:06,679 --> 01:43:08,670
Conditioning yourself to remember.

1174
01:43:08,748 --> 01:43:11,342
- Learning through repetition. - Sammy let his wife kill herself.

1175
01:43:11,417 --> 01:43:16,480
- Sammy ended up in an institution. - Sammy was a con man, a faker.

1176
01:43:16,556 --> 01:43:18,751
I never said that Sammy was faking.

1177
01:43:18,825 --> 01:43:21,988
You exposed him for what he was... a fraud.

1178
01:43:22,061 --> 01:43:24,928
But I was wrong. That's the whole point.

1179
01:43:24,997 --> 01:43:28,262
- See, Sammy's wife came to me. - Sammy didn't have a wife.

1180
01:43:31,003 --> 01:43:34,166
It was your wife who had diabetes.

1181
01:43:39,712 --> 01:43:42,306
Ouch.

1182
01:43:42,381 --> 01:43:45,009
My wife wasn't diabetic.

1183
01:43:45,084 --> 01:43:47,018
You sure?

1184
01:43:52,225 --> 01:43:55,991
- Ouch. Cut it out. - She wasn't diabetic.

1185
01:43:56,062 --> 01:44:00,158
You think I don't know my own wife? What the fuck is wrong with you?

1186
01:44:00,233 --> 01:44:03,669
Well, I guess I can only make you remember the things you wanna be true.

1187
01:44:03,736 --> 01:44:06,136
- Like old Jimmy down there. - He's not the right guy.

1188
01:44:06,205 --> 01:44:08,366
He was to you.

1189
01:44:08,441 --> 01:44:10,875
Come on. You got your revenge. Enjoy it while you still remember.

1190
01:44:10,943 --> 01:44:14,470
What difference does it make whether he was your guy or not?

1191
01:44:14,547 --> 01:44:16,674
- It makes all the difference. - Why? You're never gonna know.

1192
01:44:16,749 --> 01:44:20,082
- Yes, I will. I will. - No, you won't. - Somehow I'll know.

1193
01:44:20,152 --> 01:44:22,586
- You won't remember! - When it's done, I will know. It'll be different.

1194
01:44:22,655 --> 01:44:25,749
Well, I thought so too. In fact, I was sure of it, but you didn't!

1195
01:44:28,394 --> 01:44:32,626
That's right. The real John G.

1196
01:44:32,698 --> 01:44:35,963
I helped you find him over a year ago. He's already dead.

1197
01:44:36,035 --> 01:44:39,835
- Don't lie to me anymore. - Look, Lenny.

1198
01:44:39,906 --> 01:44:42,773
I was the cop assigned to your wife's case. I believed you.

1199
01:44:42,842 --> 01:44:45,402
I thought you deserved a chance for revenge.

1200
01:44:45,478 --> 01:44:48,470
